<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-553-541  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 553 541.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Oct 29 1990 v7 n44 p11(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T to streamline SDN billing and provisioning. (Software DefinedNetwork)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Briere, Daniel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>ATandamp;T is announcing changes to its Software-Defined Network (SDN)service that will reduce bill mailing periods by as many as fourdays and installation time by as much as 60 days.andP;  The company isopening a new Billing Support Center (BSC) and will implement newprovisioning procedures that will allow SDN customers to add SDNlocations faster and receive more current bill details.andP;  ATandamp;T ishoping that the new billing system, as well as other changes inprocedures, will make bills arrive on time and correctinaccuracies.andP;  The company will implement a new process that willdecrease the provisioning interval for switched access locationsfrom the existing 60 to 90 days down to just 30 days.andP;  ATandamp;T ismaking changes in its billing architecture by adopting aparallel-structured process where usage and access data iscollected and rated separately and then added together.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Services).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     Billing-InvoicingNetwork ArchitectureTelecommunications Services.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>